      • addMentorshipApplication

        public MessageResponse addMentorshipApplication​(MentorshipApplication application)

        Apply For A Mentorship -- Service

        This function is called from controller class. Since this is an insert operation, parameter application is a brand new object, yet its fields may be null.

        First, we check whether applicant and subjects are valid. If not return error, otherwise continue with checking database that whether this application already exists. If exists return error, otherwise save this new application to database and return "SUCCESS".

        Parameters:
        application - : Contains the information of applicant, subject and experience of applicant upon subject.
        Returns:
        MessageResponse: Returns "SUCCESS" after successful operation or "ERROR" with a reason.
        See Also:
        MentorshipApplication, MessageResponse

                                                   Users mentor)

        Delete a Mentorship -- Service

        This function is called from controller class. First we check whether parameters are null. If they are return error, otherwise delete the application.
        Parameters:
        subject - : Contains the information of the subject.
        mentor - : Contains the information of the applicant.
        Returns:
        MessageResponse: Returns "SUCCESS" after successful operation or "ERROR" with a reason.
        See Also:
        Subject, Users

      • findSubjectsUserCanEnrollAsAMentee

        public java.util.List<MentorshipApplication> findSubjectsUserCanEnrollAsAMentee​(java.lang.String mentee)

        List All Mentorship Applications a Mentee Can Enroll -- Service

        Users can see all the subjects and their mentors they can enroll.

        First we find the subjects that user already enrolled as mentee. Then we find all the approved applications. Set difference of these gives us the applications that user can enroll as a mentee.

        Parameters:
        mentee - Username of the mentee.
        Returns:
        List: Returns the subjects and mentors offered that mentee can apply .
        See Also:
        ApplicationDTO

        Approve a Mentorship Application -- Service

        First we check whether application exists and active. Return error if not. If found, its status will be changed to "approved".
        Parameters:
        applicationDTO - : Information of the application.
        Returns:
        MessageResponse: SUCCESS upon successful operation, ERROR with an explanation otherwise.
